{"name": "psrcal", "metadata": {"name": "psrcal", "version": "0.0.2", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/luferrer/psr-calibration", "license": "", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["matplotlib", "numpy", "scipy", "torch"], "summary": "Methods for evaluating and fixing calibration", "upload_time": 1693486360}, "documentation": ["# Proper Scoring Rules for calibration.\n\nThis repository contains the code for doing calibration on multi-class and binary classification using various approaches. The core functionality was written by Niko Brummer. Sergio Alvarez and I later added various methods and scripts to experiment with them. Further, I have another repository called [expected_cost](https://github.com/luferrer/expected_cost.git) with lots of examples on how to use the libraries in this repository. \n\n## How to install\n\n```\npip install psrcal\n```\n\nWhen you do that, torch, matplotlib and other libraries will also be installed, unless you already have the required versions in your system. It does not install joblib and ternary, which are only needed to run the scripts in the experiments dir. If you want to run those scripts, you can install those two packages separately. \n\nAlternatively, if you want the latest version of the code, you can:\n\n1. Clone the repository:  \n\n   ```git clone https://github.com/luferrer/psr-calibration.git```\n\n2. Install the requirements (this does install joblib and ternary since it assumes you are probably cloning the repo in order to run the scripts inside the experiments dir):  \n   \n   ```pip install -r requirements.txt```\n   \n3. Add the resulting top directory in your PYTHONPATH. In bash this would be:\n\n   ```export PYTHONPATH=ROOT_DIR/psr-calibration:$PYTHONPATH```\n\nwhere ROOT_DIR is the absolute path (or the relative path from the directory where you have the scripts or notebooks you want to run) to the top directory from where you did the clone above.\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "psrcal.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "psrcal.utils.onehot_encode", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "X", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "n_classes", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "psrcal.utils.softmax", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "x", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "axis", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "psrcal.utils.check_label", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "label", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "dims", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "psrcal.__init.__", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "psrcal", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "psrcal.optim.example", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "psrcal.optim.example.obj", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "psrcal.optim.example.Obj", "bases": ["LBFGS_Objective"], "methods": [{"name": "psrcal.optim.example.Obj.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "psrcal.optim.example.Obj.loss", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "psrcal.optim", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "psrcal.optim.vecmodule", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "psrcal.optim.vecmodule.lbfgs", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "obj", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "maxiters", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "quiet", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "psrcal.optim.vecmodule.VecModule", "bases": ["Module"], "methods": [{"name": "psrcal.optim.vecmodule.VecModule.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "psrcal.optim.vecmodule.VecModule.trainable_parameters", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["This is a generator (i.e. iterator), that returns all of the trainable\nparameters in this module, and recursively in all contained modules.\n\nIf you want all parameters instead, use self.parameters(), as in any\nModule."]}, {"name": "psrcal.optim.vecmodule.VecModule.set_paramvec", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "paramvec", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "zero_grad", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Writes the given numpy vector into the trainable parameters"]}, {"name": "psrcal.optim.vecmodule.VecModule.get_paramvec", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Extracts the trainable parameters as a numpy vector"]}, {"name": "psrcal.optim.vecmodule.VecModule.get_gradvec", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Extracts the current accumulated gradient of the trainable parameters \nas a numpy vector"]}, {"name": "psrcal.optim.vecmodule.VecModule.set_evalmode", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Stores requires_grad for each parameter into self.flags, so that we\ncan later revert to trainmode again. Then sets requires_grad = False\nfor all parmeters and sets grad=None for all parameters."]}, {"name": "psrcal.optim.vecmodule.VecModule.set_trainmode", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Reverts to trainmode by recovering requires_grad for each parmeter\nfrom the stored flags. Sets grad=None for each parameter."]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["This subclass of torch.nn.Module provides a convenient interface to a \nvectorized view of all the trainable parameters in the module. The \ntrainable parameters are those that have requires_grad=True."]}, {"name": "psrcal.optim.vecmodule.LBFGS_Objective", "bases": ["VecModule"], "methods": [{"name": "psrcal.optim.vecmodule.LBFGS_Objective.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "psrcal.optim.vecmodule.LBFGS_Objective.__call__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "paramvec", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "psrcal.optim.vecmodule.LBFGS_Objective.loss", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["This is a Module and a VecModule. You should implement a subclass to serve\nas LBFGS optimization objective. You should implement a method called\nloss, with signature loss(self) that returns the objective value. Gradient \nwill be done automatically by torch. To retrieve a vector of parameters,\nuse yourmodule.get_params(). The to-vbe-optimized optimized params include \nall members wrapped as Parameter and all Params in members that are also \nModules."]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "psrcal.optim.fullbatch_optim", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "psrcal.optim.fullbatch_optim.train_obj_scipy_lbfgs", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "obj", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "paramvec0", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "maxiters", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "quiet", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Minimizes the given objective using scipy L-BFGS-B. \n\nInputs:\n    obj: maps paramvec --> loss, gradient  (input and outputs are numpy)\n    paramvec0: a numpy vector to initialize the optimnization\n\nReturns: \n    \n    - the final paramvec \n    - the final minimum objective value \n    - a list of objective values per iteration (the training curve)\n    "]}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "psrcal.optim.fullbatch_optim.Callback", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "psrcal.optim.fullbatch_optim.Callback.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "psrcal.optim.fullbatch_optim.Callback.__call__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*p", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "psrcal.optim.fullbatch_optim.Callback.record_score", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "score", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["A small tool for tracking iterations. Not of direct concern to the user.\n\nObjects of this class can be passed as callback to scipy.optimize.minimize()."]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "psrcal.psr", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "psrcal.psr.logcost", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "q", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "label", "type": null, "default"